article.description: Daniel Amigo scored 22 points, C.J. Bobbitt drilled the game winning 3-pointer at the buzzer, and Denver outlasted Fort Wayne 76-73 in overtime on Saturday night.
article.headline: Bobbitt drills 3 at the buzzer to push Denver by Fort Wayne
article.linkText: Bobbitt drills 3 at the buzzer to push Denver by Fort Wayne
article.story: DENVER -- Daniel Amigo scored 22 points, C.J. Bobbitt drilled the game winning 3-pointer at the buzzer, and Denver outlasted Fort Wayne 76-73 in overtime on Saturday night. A Bobbitt free throw tied it at 69 and sent the game to OT. After Denver (15-9, 7-4 Summit League) fell behind by two in the extra period, a pair of Amigo free throws and a Thomas Neff jumper gave the Pioneers a 73-71 lead with 1:37 to go. After 1:26 with no scoring, the Mastodons' Brent Calhoun tied it at 73 with 11 seconds remaining, setting up Bobbitt's final second heroics. Neff finished with 21 points and Bobbitt had 12 with seven rebounds for Denver, which shot just 41.7 percent but did hit 10 3-pointers. John Konchar scored 20 to lead Fort Wayne (16-8, 5-5). Mo Evans added 18 for the Mastadons and tied the program record with 246 3-pointers made in his career.
